## TL;DR: Cushion vs Round — What Nobody Tells You

The cushion cut vs round diamond comparison is the most misunderstood in the engagement ring market. Most buyers assume round is the "safe default" and cushion is the "affordable alternative." At 1ct G-VS1 Ideal quality, the reality: a GIA G-VS1 Excellent round costs [$3,200](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28915027?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); a GIA G-VS1 Ideal cushion modified brilliant costs [$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

Round is 69% more expensive for equivalent quality.

**Contrarian Truth — The Brilliance Gap:** The extra cost of round is not buying better sparkle in the everyday sense. Round has the highest mathematical light return of any cut — but cushion has more fire (rainbow colour dispersion). These are different optical personalities, not a quality hierarchy.

Buyers who have owned both cuts and seen them in a ring, on a hand, under natural light report they cannot identify which is "more sparkly" without a side-by-side. The gap is a preference, not an objective advantage.

**Live price snapshot (Blue Nile {{year}}):**
- Round GIA G-VS1 Excellent 1ct: **[$3,200](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28915027?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Cushion Modified GIA G-VS1 Ideal 1ct: **[$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Round GIA G-VS2 Excellent 2ct: **[$16,490](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29307739?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Cushion Modified GIA G-VVS2 Ideal 2ct: **[$16,584](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28768883?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**→ The entry point for cushion buyers** who are considering switching from round: the [GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified at $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) delivers GIA-certified, Ideal cut, eye-clean VS1 quality for $1,309 less than the equivalent round. That saving funds an entire setting with budget to spare.

