## The Pillow Premium

The Pillow Premium is the price architecture of the cushion cut in the broader brilliant diamond market. Understanding it resolves the pricing surprise most cushion buyers encounter when comparing across cut types.

**Where cushion sits in the price spectrum.** In the brilliant-cut square diamond market, the price order from cheapest to most expensive is: princess cut → cushion cut → round brilliant. Princess cut G-VS1 Ideal at 1ct runs approximately $1,500–$1,700. Cushion modified brilliant G-VS1 Ideal at 1ct is [$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

Round brilliant G-VS1 Excellent at 1ct is [$3,200](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28915027?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Cushion commands a premium over princess (The Pillow Premium) but sits significantly below round.

**Why round is most expensive.** Round brilliant's price premium over cushion reflects three compounding factors: round rough diamonds waste more of the original crystal than cushion cuts (reducing yield per rough carat); round commands the highest consumer demand of any cut globally (~50-60% of all diamonds sold); and the round's technical optimisation creates an additional "brand" premium — buyers pay for the mathematical perfection. These factors combine to make round 40–80% more expensive than cushion at equivalent quality grades across the 1ct–3ct range.

**The Pillow Premium's investment implication.** Cushion cut diamonds at 1ct–2ct have lower resale values than round brilliants — the round's popularity and universal demand makes it more liquid on the secondhand market. A buyer who prioritises maximum potential resale should choose round. A buyer who prioritises quality-per-dollar in the primary purchase — and who will wear the ring rather than sell it — has a compelling financial case for cushion.

![Cushion vs Round Diamond: The Pillow Premium — price ladder princess to cushion to round infographic](/images/cushion-vs-round-pillow-premium.avif)

